reviewText: GREAT MOVIE!  Entertaining AND (VERY) enlightening.  The premise of the movie seemed unlikely a few years ago...... now ?????  Turns out "Hope and Change" doesn't mean what some thought!

Both movie's are great. Patrick does a great job of acting. I would recommend this to anyone who enjoys Patrick Swayze's acting abilities. Other than Ghost and Dirty Dancing, these movies are right up there.

Heard about Red Dawn forever, finally bought this combo for like $5, not the current price of $17. I guess I can see why it's raved about, but come on. You have to be completely in the dark about the real world to imagine this happening. And if it did, that the response of the US would be like this. Frankly, I'm amazed that it isn't panned as being completely naive and paranoid. But whatever, folks like it. Didn't watch Navy Seals at all. Tossed the dvd overboard after watching Red Dawn (was on my sailboat, had brought this to watch on my laptop). But I'm giving it 5-stars cuz I only do 5 or 1, love something or hate it, no in between. It's not a 1 so 5 is what it gets. Thought Swayze sucked in this, and would consider him a hack actor if not for Point Break with Keanu Reeves, one of the great movies of all time.

Yeah, neither one of these movies is a classic, but they are guilty pleasures.  Of the two, the Red Dawn story line strains credibility the most, yet is the best acted of the two films.  Every character in Red Dawn is believable, and the ending will tear your heart out.

Navy Seals is the classic style military shoot em' up with elite U.S. soldiers invading terrorist encampments in the mideast. Very good movie. Blackhawk Down is better though. Now to the GOOD one. RED DAWN IS ONE OF MY FAVORITE MOVIES REGARDLESS OF CATEGORY, EVER. The opener should send chills down your spine because some of this HAS ALREADY HAPPENED. Cuban and Russian forces land on U.S. soil(you read that right) and take over about one state's worth of land. A small group of teenagers fight for their lives in the mountains with Cubans in military like gunfights. Tanks, grenades, machine guns, everything. Once again, read the opening lines VERY CAREFULLY and realize:THIS COULD ACTUALLY HAPPEN NOW. You call Red Dawn a movie? Me and a lot of other people call it a SURVIVAL MANUAL. THIS MOVIE COULD SAVE YOUR LIFE. I mean it. Highest possible recommendation!
